⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Droplet
node DRP · DRP · ⟦The Droplet:DRP:86ab11⟧

WHO   — The Droplet — a perfect mirror that kills — the strong-force probe
WHAT  — A small (~3.5 m) teardrop Trisolaran probe whose hull is made of 'strong-interaction-force material' — giving it a perfectly mirror-smooth, near-absolute-zero, indestructible surface. In the Doomsday Battle it rams straight through Earth's combined space fleet, destroying roughly two thousand warships in minutes.
WHERE — 3BT · The Technologia of Trisolaris  Framework inputs: Remembrance of Earth's Past + adaptations; real-science verdict  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — The Droplet's annihilation of the fleet is a book-two set-piece; Netflix brings it forward into season one. (Tencent's 2023 series adapts book one only, so its full battle is still to come there.)
HOW   — FLUFF. The strong nuclear force acts only at femtometre range — you cannot build a macroscopic hull out of it. A flawless, frictionless, indestructible mirror is fantasy. The honest nod: ultra-dense degenerate matter (white-dwarf / neutron-star material) is real, and unimaginably strong — but it is not a teardrop you can fly through a fleet.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  They saw me approach and called me a gift. I went through their two thousand ships like a needle through smoke.

spoken token : nom-min-daem   ·   hex : 86ab11
